                            <comment id="11466" author="lope" created="Sun, 12 Mar 2017 05:50:12 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;I tried to use sockets using Perfect and lacking comprehensive documentation and tutorials it was long trial&amp;amp;error experience. I managed to make connection between two running processes that communicate between themselves over socket connection, but I have a problem I don&apos;t know how to solve. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I read data by running this piece of code on separate thread:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;repeat {&lt;br/&gt;
	self.remoteConnection.readSomeBytes(count: self.readByteCount) { bytes in&lt;br/&gt;
		if let bytes = bytes, bytes.count &amp;gt; 0 &lt;/p&gt;
{
			// do something with the data
		}
&lt;p&gt; else {&lt;br/&gt;
			if bytes == nil &lt;/p&gt;
{
				self.connected = false
				print(&quot;server disconnected&quot;)
			}
&lt;p&gt;		}&lt;br/&gt;
	}&lt;br/&gt;
} while self.connected&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;this works, but it causes my process to eat all available cpu since it is looping all the time. Is there a way how to change this into blocking read that would execute only when there is actually some data to read?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am sorry if this is not a proper channel to ask questions like this, if so, please let me know where to go&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="11546" author="rocky" created="Mon, 24 Apr 2017 11:36:04 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, please join us on our Slack to ask such questions: &lt;a href=&quot;http://perfect.ly/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://perfect.ly&lt;/a&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the best reading / sending procedure on socket is using select() method, as illustration below:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/select.2.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://man7.org/linux/man-pages/man2/select.2.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Would you mind me asking why do you wanna use raw socket, please?&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Warm,&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Rocky.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
